    <briefdescription>
<para>Header file of Finite State Machine (FSM) for firmware updates. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Project </title><para>AXO Track Firmware 2023</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="copyright"><para>(c) 2023 AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. All rights reserved.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="author"><para>AXO Track GmbH, Berlin (Germany)</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>This header file defines the Finite State Machine (FSM) for handling firmware updates in the AXO X1 device. It provides the state transitions and event handling mechanisms necessary for managing the different stages of firmware updates, including OTA commands, firmware info handling, download, and restart. The FSM is implemented using a set of state classes that encapsulate the behavior of each state.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>This source code is confidential and proprietary information of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. You may not disclose, copy, or distribute this source code or any part thereof without the explicit permission </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
